3 different games are played: mah-jongg, snooker, monopoly
3 different pets are kept: horse, chinchilla, goat
The people grow 3 different varities of flowers: tulip, dahlia, begonia
1. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left of the person who growsdahlia##1
2. the person driving the helicopter is on the left of the person playing monopoly##1
3. the person who growstulip is the person who's birthday is in january##1
4. the person who's birthday is in november is on the right of the person drinking sprite##1
5. the owner of the chinchilla is the person drinking water##1
6. the person driving the bus is on the left of the owner of the horse##1
7. the person driving the bus is on the far left##1
8. the person playing snooker is the person driving the bus##1
9. the person drinking mirinda is in the middle##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1    |     2      |      3       |
| Beverage          | sprite  | mirinda       | water    |
| Birthday         | january | november     | december      |
| Transport           | bus  | helicopter | roller    |
